NGX Regulation (NGXReg)- the regulatory arm of the Nigerian Exchange (NGX), has lifted suspension placed on the shares of Tourist Company of Nigeria (TCN) Plc. The NGX had suspended TCN and three other companies on July 2, last year for failure to submit their financial statements in line with corporate governance rules at the Exchange.   Pan African Towers lists N10b debut bond     Dufil Prima Foods eyes N30b short-term capital     Transcorp grows net profit by 147% in Q1   NGXReg stated that TCN has  submitted its audited financial statements for 2020 and 2021 as well as interim unaudited financial statements for the first quarter ended March 31, 2022. The suspension placed on TCN’s shares was consequently lifted on May 11, 2022.